---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Megan Lange">
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Megan Lange</p>
    <h1>Product manager. Platform builder. Compulsive shipper.</h1>
    <p class="tagline">Senior product manager &middot; consumer commerce &middot; gaming platforms</p>
    <p>
      Most recently at Microsoft on the Xbox Consumer Commerce Platform team. My work has
      centered on cross-cutting capabilities in the commerce lifecycle: subscription lifecycle,
      regulatory compliance, retail federation, and the systems that keep them running at scale.
    </p>
    <p>
      Recent highlight: I built the Sub + Title subscription-bundle platform capability that
      powered a AAA publisher's global pre-order launch (Rockstar's GTA VI) &mdash; a rolling
      release across 20+ countries that landed with zero platform-tracked issues. Other recent
      focus areas: Consumer REM (a regulatory program spanning financial crime, order-to-cash,
      and stored-value compliance), CSV / gift-card product ownership, OEM Digital Attach, and
      the transactional-email infrastructure behind Xbox, Store, and Office.
    </p>
    <p class="dim">
      I'm also an AI-native PM &mdash; I author shared GitHub Copilot skills my teammates use and
      lean on agentic workflows to accelerate the highest-leverage product work.
    </p>
    <p class="dim">
      Recently impacted by the July 2026 Microsoft layoff and exploring what's next.
    </p>
    <nav class="cta">
      <a href="/about/">about &rarr;</a>
      <a href="/projects/">projects &rarr;</a>
      <a href="/writing/">writing &rarr;</a>
    </nav>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .hero {
    padding-top: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .tagline {
    margin-top: -0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }
  .cta {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
  }
  .cta a {
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
</style>
